3rd and final try on selling this rag-price dropped again.  This is a used Kimber .45ACP, 5" barrel, with the traditional internal extractor, meprolight nite sights (a call to Kimber indicated that this gun was made in July 2008).  I am the second owner of this pistol-I purchased it from another guy here on Armslist.

My first trip to the range and the gun has hammer follow and double fires.  I believe the problem lies in the sear and hammer engagement (it's not as simple as a sear spring).  All internal parts appear to be original, the slide to frame fit is tight, the barrel is in good shape, the plunger tube is tight as well.  The gun is in really good shape except for a slight mar near the slide release (newbie field strip mistake) and the mag release is a little scratched on the ejection port side.  The gun comes with 2 Kimber 7 rd. mags, bushing wrench, and a brand new Kimber steel mainspring housing that I bought and never installed.

Just to eliminate any liability on my end (do to the double firing-"full auto" effect), I am selling this gun without the firing pin-making it 100% inoperable. 

I am moving to Kentucky/getting a Kentucky driver's license later this week so Ohio buyers have a very truncated time table for FTF.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Bushmaster AR15 M4A3 Carbine - For Sale or Trade
postcontent:
Bushmaster (pre-ban) gas piston upper on a Liberty Tactical lower. The gas piston is the same system used in AK47's and FAL's, this functions with a wider range of ammunition - using less gas pressure - and reduces maintenance to a minimum. Excess heat, carbon build up, and gas leaks are eliminated in a system with lower cyclic rate; improved reliability and control; reduced heat and maintenance.Carbon build up and powder residue are prevented from fouling the Upper Receiver - a superior operating system.

Barrel - is 5.56 Nato, so it can feed 5.56 or .223, 1:9 twist, chrome lined.
A3 flat top w/ the removable carry handle
A2 birdcage flash suppressor (removable)
Yankee Hill flip up front sight (removable) 
Picatinny rails mounted at the 10, 2 and 6 positions of the forend. 
Brand new Liberty Tactical lower w/ a 5 position buttstock (all USGI internals)
Bayonet lug

The upper by itself retails for $1100. Comes with a Bushmaster 30rd mag, a 30rd Magpul Pmag, Bushmaster padded hardside carry case, a 2 point sling, removable carry handle and an NcStar red dot sight.

I know $1300 is expensive, but check out the gas piston AR's online they average about $1600, if they have them in stock, and many of them are even higher than that. Many are going for over $2000. This is NOT a conversion gas piston. It is a true gas piston AR15.

TRADES- I am looking for handguns in trade. Trades in the range of about $1200 to $1300. I will take one handgun plus cash to make up the difference in value, or two handguns also if they are in the dollar range shown above. If you have something that you think I might be interested in, but doesn't reach the dollar amount, just let me know. Maybe we can work something out. Special interest in compact 1911's, compact or subcompact Glocks, compact M&P 9 or 40, Sig P238, Kahr CM9, Diamondback 380.

I use the Blue Book Value of Guns to determine your guns worth. I will usually give 100% value unless something major is wrong with the gun. I am not going to be critical over a little scratch or light holster wear. I can go above book value too. If I am really interested in the gun (like the guns listed above). 

This is the last run for this AR, if no deal is made it will return to the safe. Don't miss the chance to own a gas piston AR for cheap.

title: For Sale:  1940's Stevens model 311  12ga. double barrel
postcontent:
(Antique) 1940's Stevens model 311, 5100 Made by Savage arms Corp. 12 Ga. hammerless, side by side double barrel 2 3/4 chambered,"Tenerite plastic" stock,double triggers,28 inch barrels bright and shiny no pitting or rust,44 1/2 overall length, 7 lbs.

The model 311 started as the Springfield "5000" around 1920 with the model designation changing to "5100" in 1931.Around 1941 it became the Stevens model 311.It was discontinued in 1989  Double barrels were "modified" on the right barrel, and "full choke" on the left side. Up untill 1968 they did not have serial numbers as it wasnt required.Post march 1949 models had date codes stamped between the trigger and barrel hinge pin.In1931 they were marked "5100", around 1941 they were marked as "model 311" .This one has both markings suggesting very early 40's mfg. maybe.This one has an "A" inside a circle,under the barrels on the receiver which would seem to be a "1949" model, but from what i've read on these the "5100" marking wasnt used affter the early 40's.

No it is not a pump shotgun,or chambered for 3" magnums.
